+    // (zc patch) On AArch64 the trampoline is placed right after the branch
+    // instead of at the extra block (the end of the function). A conditional
+    // branch (b.cond) only reaches +/-1 MB; in a function that emits more
+    // code than that, retargeting it to an end-of-function trampoline makes
+    // the branch unencodable (InvalidDisplacement at label bind). Layout:
+    //
+    //     b.cond trampoline      ; 8 bytes away - always encodable
+    //     b      skipLabel       ; fall-through path jumps over the fixups
+    //   trampoline:
+    //     <register-state fixup moves>
+    //     b      savedTarget     ; +/-128 MB - reaches anywhere
+    //   skipLabel:
+    //     <original fall-through>
+    //
+    // This costs the fall-through path one unconditional branch whenever the
+    // edge needs fixups, which x86 avoids with the end-of-function placement,
+    // so that path is kept for x86 (jcc reaches +/-2 GB there).
+    //
+    // Inserted nodes are not re-visited: the caller captured node->next()
+    // before calling allocBranch, and the consecutive-block fixups emitted
+    // after this returns use afterLast->prev() as the cursor, which is now
